  "id": "019d2eb4-36fb-7ab1-a996-d76665446f50",
  "content": "## Retention Scoring Module (Issue #15)\n\nImplemented `crates/corvia-kernel/src/scoring.rs` — pure computation module for tiered knowledge lifecycle scoring.\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n- **RetentionParams struct** instead of passing KnowledgeEntry directly: keeps scoring decoupled from storage types, independently testable, no I/O coupling\n- **f64 internal math, f32 return**: precision for intermediate computation, matches the `retention_score` field type on KnowledgeEntry\n- **NaN/infinity sanitization**: all float inputs are sanitized via `sanitize_f64()` helper; NaN score returns 0.0 rather than propagating\n- **Access frequency capped at 1.0**: `min(freq, 1.0)` prevents u32::MAX access_count from blowing out the component range\n- **Alpha=0 short-circuit**: Structural entries skip `powf()` entirely since `(1+t)^0 = 1.0` always\n\n### Formula\n`retention_score = 0.35×D(t,α) + 0.30×A(count,recency) + 0.20×G(edges) + 0.15×C(conf)`\n- Superseded entries get 0.5× penalty\n- Structural + superseded uses α=0.60 (Episodic rate) instead of α=0\n\n### Hysteresis Thresholds\nDemotion and promotion thresholds have gaps to prevent oscillation:\n- Hot→Warm at &lt;0.50, Warm→Hot at ≥0.60 (gap: 0.50-0.60)\n- Warm→Cold at &lt;0.25, Cold→Warm at ≥0.35 (gap: 0.25-0.35)\n- Cold→Forgotten at &lt;0.05 (terminal, no recovery)\n\n### Test Coverage\n46 tests covering: RFC worked examples, NaN/infinity/u32::MAX edge cases, exact boundary thresholds, component unit tests, weight sum invariant.\n\nPR: #32",
